{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This Term Frequency (TF) counts the number of articles (titles and abstracts) containing the term rather the number of occurrences of the term to prevent individual articles from having undue influence on the result.",
    "The TF was then multiplied by the Inverse Document Frequency (IDF) to get a TF-IDF vector for each journal (Manning et al., 2008).",
    "The IDF of a term i is log(N∕n i), where N is the overall number of journals and n i is the number of journals containing term i.",
    "The TF-IDF score of a term in a journal is therefore high if the term occurs in many of that journal's articles but in few other journals' articles.",
    "Conversely, a term's TF-IDF score is low if it is either rare in the journal or occurs in most other journals."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The TF was then multiplied by the Inverse Document Frequency (IDF) to get a TF-IDF vector for each journal (Manning et al., 2008)."
  ]
}